/*
1. Nets: Nets are continously driven by the combinational logic circuits.
it means it cannot store any value.

represented by "wire" 
default value of net is 'Z' (high impedence)

******
wire a,b,y;
assign y = a & b;
********

2. Regs: Reg is different form hardware register.

Declaring a Reg doesn't mean declaring a flip flop or a latch 
but it represents a storage element unlike net.

use only through procedural statements

************
reg a,b,y;
always@(posedge clock)
 begin
  y = a &b; 
 end
 *****************
*/
